	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_46883751"><p>It actually refers to his head. Like the one on his shoulders, not the the other kind... French likes to have the letter "s" silent and modifying how other letters are pronounced, mostly the "e". In modern French, the word for head is t&#234;te. Most words with &#234; now used to have es in them. F&#234;te = feste = festival. Arr&#234;t = Arrest, etc.</p></div>
	</div>

